Then it follows that if H. E. grows less , the ratio of lift to drift must do the same . 
A , B , and C are front views of three surfaces . 
A has its full H. E. , and therefore , from the point of view from which we are at the moment considering efficiency , it has its best lift drift ratio . 
B and C both possess the same surface as A , but one is inclined upwards from its centre and the other is straight but tilted . 
